To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 6,476,677.56
- Total Revenue = 22,876,677.56

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{6,476,677.56}{22,876,677.56} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.2831 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 28.31\% \]

Therefore, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '28.31%'} }
```
